  <h2>Getting Started</h2>

  <h3>Installation</h3>
  <p>
    Download ColorClip Pro for your platform (macOS or Windows) from the
    <a href="/">homepage</a>. Follow the <a href="/docs/installation">installation guide</a>
    for platform-specific instructions.
  </p>

  <h3>First Launch</h3>
  <p>
    When you first launch ColorClip Pro, you'll see an empty palette. You can start
    adding colors immediately or sign in to enable cloud sync across your devices.
  </p>

  <h2>Key Features</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Unlimited Palettes</strong> - Create and organize up to 256 swatches per palette</li>
    <li><strong>Screen Eyedropper</strong> - Pick colors from anywhere on your screen</li>
    <li><strong>Cloud Sync</strong> - Sync palettes across all your devices in real-time</li>
    <li><strong>Multiple Formats</strong> - Copy colors in HEX, RGB, HSV, or normalized values</li>
    <li><strong>Color History</strong> - Track changes to each swatch over time</li>
    <li><strong>9 Languages</strong> - Available in English, Spanish, French, German, Italian, Russian, Korean, Japanese, and Chinese</li>
  </ul>

